track_notes: Time was limited as we had to catch the last ferry back to Filicudi island so we were in a hurry. The climb was quite quick as the rocky stairs until Pianicello were in a good condition. The upper part of the path is a little bit more difficult. In the end you walk beside an old volcano crater to get to the summit. The Icom IC-705 and the end fed vertical for 20m worked fine during my second SOTA activity ever. In the end we reached the ferry just in time.
